content: Needs it badly

Put simply this game is fantastic. High caliber zombie splatterin' fun. It takes what would be a huge downside in any other game and makes it an asset. Eg. "Thermal imaging"-gameplay is in monochrome and if you've used military grade thermals you know the limited imaging it can present. The rewards system is better than any phone/tablet game I've seen. If you're the lazy type, purchase prices for coins don't exactly add up as the quantity goes up but if you do a little a math that can be to your advantage.

The AC-130 mission in Call of Duty's 4: Modern Warefare was one of my favourite ever. This game runs flawlessly. There hasn't been a single problem I've ran into nor do I have any complaint whatsoever. The game is everything it can be. But.. Hey, what's up with the low-quality menu graphics and AC-130 animation? Elementary stuff -- Four Stars.
